<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910329-0037</DOCNO><DOCID>910329-0037.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Noxso Corp.:   Concern, With Others, Gets   $33 Million Government Job</HL><DATE>03/29/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B3B</SO><CO>   NOXO MRN GRA OEC</CO><IN>ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)POLLUTION CONTROL, WASTE MANAGEMENT SERVICES (POL)INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL SERVICES (SVC)</IN><GV>ENERGY DEPARTMENT (ERG)</GV><LP>   Noxso Corp., Bethel Park, Pa., said the company and agroup of others have received a $33 million governmentcontract to build a system to reduce pollutants at an Ohiopower plant.   The group also includes Morrison Knudson Corp.'sMK-Ferguson division, W.R. Grace andamp; Co. and Ohio Edison Co.</LP><TEXT>   The project is for a commercial demonstration of Noxso'sacid rain abatement system, which removes pollutants fromcoal-fired power plants.   The U.S. Department of Energy award covers half of theproject's cost, with the rest coming from the companies andresearch grants. Construction of the project at Ohio Edison'sNiles, Ohio, plant will begin late next year.   Noxso develops acid rain control technology.</TEXT></DOC>